  "body": "London specification: https://github.com/ethereum/eth1.0-specs/blob/master/network-upgrades/mainnet-upgrades/london.md\r\n\r\n| EIP | PR | Status|  \r\n| --- | --- | ---| \r\n| [1559](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1559) (Fee market change)| #22837 #22896| Merged  Merged  |\r\n| [3198](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3198) (BASEFEE opcode)| #22837 | Merged | \r\n| [3228](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3554) (:bomb: delay)| https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/22840 and https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/22870 |  Merged -- needs [update](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/pull/3563) to `9.7M` |\r\n| [3529](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3529) (alternative refund reduction)| #22733| Merged|\r\n| [3541](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/8aa8b36070c28808f32d1e6465e71e9d0f2b8d2f/EIPS/eip-3541.md) (Reject new contracts starting with the 0xEF byte) | https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/22809 | Merged | \r\n\r\nAlso: london + baikal definnitions: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/22822 (merged)\r\n\r\nAs of now, it should be possible to run `baikal` off of #22837\r\n",
